# Read this entire file before writing any code. Follow every rule strictly.

## Project Overview

GetAnyNumberOnline is a temporary SMS verification number platform.
Users buy temporary phone numbers, receive OTP codes, and rent numbers long-term.
Stack: Next.js 15 (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Supabase, Flutterwave, SMSPool API, Vercel.

---

## Tech Stack — Strict Versions

- Next.js 15 with App Router — never use Pages Router patterns
- TypeScript — strict mode, no `any` unless absolutely unavoidable, always type it explicitly
- Tailwind CSS — utility classes only, no custom CSS files unless absolutely necessary
- Supabase — Auth, Postgres, Realtime, Edge Functions — the ONLY backend layer
- @supabase/ssr — for all Supabase client creation, never @supabase/auth-helpers
- Flutterwave React SDK — flutterwave-react-v3 for payments
- SMSPool REST API — for phone number provisioning
- Vercel — deployment platform
- Package manager: pnpm

