## Pricing Markup Rules

### One-time numbers:

```typescript
function applyMarkup(rawPrice: number): number {
  let markup: number;
  if (rawPrice < 0.1) markup = 0.4;
  else if (rawPrice <= 0.3) markup = 0.3;
  else markup = 0.2;
  return Math.ceil(rawPrice * (1 + markup) * 100) / 100;
}
```

### Rentals:

```typescript
function applyRentalMarkup(raw: number): number {
  return Math.ceil(raw * 1.35 * 100) / 100;
}
```

Apply markup BOTH when displaying price to the user AND when deducting from balance. Both must use the same markup calculation — never show one price and charge another.

