## Next.js App Router Rules

- Use Server Components by default
- Add 'use client' only when needed (useState, useEffect, event handlers, browser APIs)
- Never use getServerSideProps or getStaticProps — those are Pages Router
- API routes in src/app/api/{name}/route.ts
- Middleware in middleware.ts at project root
- Dynamic params are Promises in Next.js 15 — always await them:

```typescript
// Correct:
const { id } = await params;
// Wrong:
const { id } = params;
```

- Loading states: use loading.tsx files or Suspense boundaries
- Error states: use error.tsx files

---

## Auth Rules

- Supabase email/password auth only (no OAuth for now)
- Session stored in localStorage under `sb-{project-ref}-auth-token`
- Middleware protects all /dashboard/\* routes
- After sign-in: router.push('/dashboard') + router.refresh()
- After sign-out: redirect to '/'
- Never redirect to /auth from inside dashboard components — let middleware handle it

---

## Code Quality Rules

- Never use `any` type — always define proper interfaces
- Always handle loading states on async operations
- Always handle error states with user-facing messages
- Never leave console.log in production code — use console.error for actual errors only
- Always use try/catch on async operations
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks in src/hooks/
- Keep components under 200 lines — extract sub-components if needed
- Always show price BEFORE user confirms an order
- Always confirm before destructive actions (cancel, delete)

